# 4. デートの日まで

Saki: Hmmhmm♪ Hehe♪
Saki: Which one should I wear...?
Tsukasa's Voice: Saki, can I come in?
Saki: Sure♪
Tsukasa: I just wanted to ask... Whoa, why are your clothes all over the place? Are you starting a fashion show or something?
Saki: No, I'm just picking out what to wear for a date.
Tsukasa: D-Date?!
Tsukasa: D-D-Date?!
Tsukasa: Of course...! You're not a little girl anymore....!!
Tsukasa: Whatever you do, you'll have my full support. Follow your heart!
Saki: What? Tsukasa, hold on! Why are you giving me a “dad speech”?
Saki: I'm just going out with Ichi and the others!
Tsukasa: With Ichika and...? Oh, your bandmates...
Saki: Was there something you wanted to ask me?
Tsukasa: Yes, it's about your plans for the next weekend. Everyone else is going to be away on a trip.
Tsukasa: I'm doing a show then, so I won't be home either. I was worried about leaving you all alone in case something happened.
Saki: Well, you don't have to worry because I'm going out with my bandmates on Saturday!
Tsukasa: Great, so you'll have company.
Saki: And anyway, you worry too much! The doctor said I was fine.
Tsukasa: That's true, but...
Saki: I AM FINE! You can go out and enjoy your weekend without being so concerned about me.
Tsukasa: Okay, I got it. Just... Remember to look both ways before you cross the road!
Saki: I will!
Saki: Tsukasa, you're such a worrywart.
Saki: Hmm... It'd be terrible if I came down with something before then...
Saki: As much as I enjoy my club and my job, I should take it easy. I'll go to bed early tonight.
Soft Tennis Club Captain: Okay, team. Good work today!
Saki: Thank you! See you next time!
Honami: Hi, Saki. Is the soft tennis club done for the day?
Saki: Yeah. The home ec club too? Let's walk home together!
Honami: Sure!
Saki: So in the end, I decided I'll wear the shorts I bought the other day and pair them with...
Honami: Huh?
Honami: Saki, your face looks really flushed.
Saki: What? Really?
Saki: I don't feel like I'm running a fever. Maybe I applied too much blush?
Honami: I don't think that's it... Just to be safe, maybe you should check your temperature when you get back home.
Saki: Yeah, I'll do that. Thanks...
Saki: But I'm sure it's nothing! My normal temperature's naturally a little higher than average.
Saki: (What if I do have a fever? Now that I think about it, I have been feeling a little out of it.)
Saki: (No matter. A good night's sleep will make it go away.)
Saki: Oof...
Saki: (I had a fever, like Hona said. I better head home early and make sure I get plenty of rest.)
Saki: Hm? It's from my boss...? “Can anyone cover these shifts?”
Saki: I thought next month's schedule wouldn't be up for a while. Why are they already looking to cover shifts?
Saki: “Our part-time staff leader, Ms. Yamada, said her child caught the flu and urgently needs to take a week off from work.” Whaaat?!
Saki: “Please let me know ASAP if you can take any of her shifts.”
Saki: It looks like they're struggling with finding someone to cover Saturday, but that's the day we're going to the observatory...
Saki: Well, I'm busy on that day...
Saki: H-Hello, this is Saki speaking.
Manager: “I'm sorry about the sudden call. Have you seen my message? Ms. Yamada's not coming in this week. Could you cover her shift on Saturday?”
Saki: I'm sorry, but I can't do Saturday...
Manager: “What about today? I've got someone who can take the Saturday shift if you can swap with them today.”
Saki: Um...
Saki: (I'll probably be okay if I make sure to pace myself. They really need my help.)
Saki: Yes, I think I can make it today!
Manager: “Really?! Thank you! You're a life-saver!”
Saki: I'll head over now!
Ichika: Hey, Saki. You don't have club activities today, so you're going straight home, right?
Saki: Sorry, Ichi! I have to cover someone's shift at the cafe. I've got to run or I won't make it. Bye!
Ichika: Oh, okay...
Saki: I have to hurry...!
Shiho: Saki?
Shiho: Where's she running off to?
Shiho: I'll have to remind her again to take it easy...
Saki: Sigh... I really have no luck today. Why did it have to be so busy at work?
Saki: And I think my fever's gotten a little worse...
Saki: Maybe I should cancel band practice tomorrow...
Shiho: There's just one condition. Don't start slacking off with band practice because of this trip.
Shiho: If I see you start to get lazy, I'm out. Got it?
Saki: If I don't go, our trip to the observatory might get canceled, too...
Saki: I have to buckle down and somehow hang on until Saturday.
